--> to differentiate it from the [[1st century]] Christian church. In April 1838, the name again was officially changed by revelation to the ''Church of Jesus Christ of Latter Day Saints'', which, in the form of the revelation published by Joseph Smith did not contain the article in the title and spelled "Latter Day" without a hypen or lower-case "d".<!--

